**Abstract:**
Brief working notes dated July 9, 1992, outlining a project to critique theology as episteme. The document proposes showing structural similarity between ethics and theology (faith), arguing that the Greek contemplator's model of knowledge is wrongheaded. It suggests that demonstrating why ethics cannot be a science will open the way to understanding faith not as speculative knowledge but as practical wisdom involving stories, history, and sacred history.

**AI Recommendation:** Important methodological outline; sketches overall project direction for Chantilly materials.

